[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Section Detection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `detect_sections(note_text)`. Clinical notes have internal structure even when they look like a wall of text. Identifying section boundaries gives us critical context for assertion classification downstream.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import re
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def detect_sections(note_text: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Split a clinical note into sections based on header patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Clinical notes use various header conventions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - ALL CAPS followed by colon: "ASSESSMENT:"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Title case followed by colon: "Assessment and Plan:"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Wrapped in asterisks: "** Family History **"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Each returned section includes its category (ACTIVE, PMH, FAMILY, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and the text content under that header.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Pattern matches common clinical note header formats.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Looks for lines that are mostly a label followed by a colon,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # or all-caps lines that serve as section dividers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     header_pattern = re.compile(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         r"^(?:"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         r"([A-Z][A-Za-z /&]+):[ ]*$"     # "Assessment and Plan:" on its own line
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         r"|([A-Z][A-Z /&]{2,}):?"         # "ASSESSMENT:" or "ASSESSMENT" (all caps)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         r"|\*\*\s*(.+?)\s*\*\*"           # "** Family History **"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         r")",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         re.MULTILINE
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sections = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     last_end = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     last_category = "UNKNOWN"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for match in header_pattern.finditer(note_text):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Save the text between the previous header and this one.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if last_end > 0 or match.start() > 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             section_text = note_text[last_end:match.start()].strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if section_text:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sections.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "category": last_category,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "text": section_text,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "start_offset": last_end
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Determine the header text from whichever capture group matched.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         header_text = match.group(1) or match.group(2) or match.group(3)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         header_text = header_text.strip().lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Classify this header.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         last_category = classify_section_header(header_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         last_end = match.end()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Don't forget the final section after the last header.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     remaining = note_text[last_end:].strip()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if remaining:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sections.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "category": last_category,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "text": remaining,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "start_offset": last_end
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # If no headers were found at all, treat the entire note as UNKNOWN.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not sections:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sections.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "category": "UNKNOWN",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "text": note_text.strip(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "start_offset": 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return sections
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_section_header(header_lower: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Map a lowercase header string to a section category.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The category determines default assertion status for problems found there.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if header_lower in ACTIVE_SECTION_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "ACTIVE"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif header_lower in PMH_SECTION_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "PMH"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif header_lower in FAMILY_SECTION_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "FAMILY"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif header_lower in RESOLVED_SECTION_HEADERS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "RESOLVED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return "UNKNOWN"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Extract Clinical Problems
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `extract_problems(sections)`. We send each relevant section to Amazon Comprehend Medical's DetectEntitiesV2 API and filter for MEDICAL_CONDITION entities. The API returns entities with traits (NEGATION, SYMPTOM, SIGN, DIAGNOSIS) that we'll use in the assertion step.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def extract_problems(sections: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run NER on each relevant section to extract MEDICAL_CONDITION entities.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We skip sections like allergies or medications that won't contain
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     problem list entries. For each extracted condition, we carry forward
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the section category so assertion classification knows where it came from.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We only process sections that might contain problem mentions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relevant_categories = {"ACTIVE", "PMH", "FAMILY", "RESOLVED", "UNKNOWN"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_problems = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for section in sections:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if section["category"] not in relevant_categories:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Comprehend Medical has a 20,000 character limit per request.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Most clinical note sections are well under this, but we truncate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # just in case. In production, you'd chunk long sections.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         text = section["text"][:20000]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if not text.strip():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Call DetectEntitiesV2. This returns all medical entity types:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # MEDICAL_CONDITION, MEDICATION, ANATOMY, TEST_TREATMENT_PROCEDURE, etc.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # We only care about MEDICAL_CONDITION for problem list extraction.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         response = comprehend_medical.detect_entities_v2(Text=text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for entity in response.get("Entities", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if entity["Category"] != "MEDICAL_CONDITION":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Build our problem record with everything we need downstream.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             problem = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "text": entity["Text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": entity["Score"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "begin_offset": entity["BeginOffset"] + section["start_offset"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "end_offset": entity["EndOffset"] + section["start_offset"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "section": section["category"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "traits": entity.get("Traits", []),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "attributes": entity.get("Attributes", []),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # entity_type helps distinguish DIAGNOSIS vs SIGN vs SYMPTOM
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "entity_type": next(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     (t["Name"] for t in entity.get("Traits", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                      if t["Name"] in ("DIAGNOSIS", "SIGN", "SYMPTOM")),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "DIAGNOSIS"  # default if no type trait present
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             all_problems.append(problem)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Extracted %d MEDICAL_CONDITION entities", len(all_problems))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return all_problems
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Classify Assertion Status
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `classify_assertions(problems)`. This is the critical gate that prevents negated conditions, family history, and hypotheticals from polluting the active problem list. We combine two signals: NER-level traits (NEGATION, HYPOTHETICAL) and section-level context.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def classify_assertions(problems: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Determine assertion status for each extracted problem.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Assertion status = is this problem actually active for this patient?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Possible values: PRESENT, NEGATED, HISTORICAL, FAMILY_HISTORY,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     HYPOTHETICAL, RESOLVED.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We use a two-layer approach:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Section context sets the baseline (a problem in "Family History" is FAMILY_HISTORY)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Entity-level traits can override (NEGATION trait overrides section context)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     classified = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for problem in problems:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Layer 1: Section context provides the default assertion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         assertion = _section_to_assertion(problem["section"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Layer 2: Entity-level traits can override.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for trait in problem["traits"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             trait_name = trait["Name"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             trait_score = trait["Score"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Only trust high-confidence traits for overrides.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if trait_score < 0.80:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if trait_name == "NEGATION":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # "No diabetes" in the Assessment section means NOT active.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Negation overrides section context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assertion = "NEGATED"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 break  # negation is definitive
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if trait_name == "HYPOTHETICAL":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # "If she develops CKD" is not an active problem.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assertion = "HYPOTHETICAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Layer 3: Resolution marker heuristic for ambiguous cases.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # If the problem text itself contains resolution language and we
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # haven't already classified it as negated/hypothetical, downgrade.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if assertion == "PRESENT":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if _has_resolution_markers(problem["text"]):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 assertion = "HISTORICAL"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         problem_with_assertion = {**problem, "assertion": assertion}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         classified.append(problem_with_assertion)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Log assertion distribution for monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     assertion_counts = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for p in classified:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         assertion_counts[p["assertion"]] = assertion_counts.get(p["assertion"], 0) + 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Assertion distribution: %s", assertion_counts)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return classified
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _section_to_assertion(section_category: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Map section category to default assertion status."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mapping = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ACTIVE": "PRESENT",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "PMH": "HISTORICAL",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "FAMILY": "FAMILY_HISTORY",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "RESOLVED": "RESOLVED",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "UNKNOWN": "PRESENT"  # conservative default: assume active
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return mapping.get(section_category, "PRESENT")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _has_resolution_markers(text: str) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Check if the problem text contains language suggesting resolution."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     text_lower = text.lower()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return any(marker in text_lower for marker in RESOLUTION_MARKERS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Normalize to Standard Codes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `normalize_problems(classified_problems)`. Active and historical problems need SNOMED CT and ICD-10-CM codes for downstream use. We call InferICD10CM and InferSNOMEDCT and keep the top 3 candidates from each.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def normalize_problems(classified_problems: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Map extracted problem text to SNOMED CT and ICD-10-CM codes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We only normalize problems that might go on the problem list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Negated and hypothetical problems don't need codes (they won't be added
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to any structured list), but we still include them in the output for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     completeness and auditability.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Only these assertion types get normalized.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     normalize_assertions = {"PRESENT", "HISTORICAL", "FAMILY_HISTORY"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     normalized = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for problem in classified_problems:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if problem["assertion"] not in normalize_assertions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Still include in output, just without codes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             normalized.append({**problem, "icd10": None, "snomed": None})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # The text we send for normalization. Comprehend Medical's inference
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # APIs work best with the exact extracted span plus a bit of context,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # but even just the entity text produces reasonable results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         text_for_inference = problem["text"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Call ICD-10-CM inference.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         icd10_codes = _infer_icd10(text_for_inference)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Call SNOMED CT inference.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         snomed_codes = _infer_snomed(text_for_inference)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         normalized.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             **problem,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "icd10": icd10_codes,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "snomed": snomed_codes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return normalized
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _infer_icd10(text: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Call InferICD10CM and return top 3 candidates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The API returns entities with ICD10CMConcepts ranked by confidence.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We take the top 3 because the top-1 isn't always correct, especially
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for abbreviations or partial mentions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical.infer_icd10_cm(Text=text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # InferICD10CM returns entities, each with a list of ICD10CMConcepts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We want the concepts from the first (most relevant) entity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = response.get("Entities", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not entities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concepts = entities[0].get("ICD10CMConcepts", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Return top 3, with the fields downstream needs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Code": c["Code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Description": c["Description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Score": round(c["Score"], 3)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for c in concepts[:3]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _infer_snomed(text: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Call InferSNOMEDCT and return top 3 candidates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Same pattern as ICD-10 inference. SNOMED codes are preferred for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     clinical problem lists because SNOMED has richer hierarchy and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     more clinical granularity than ICD-10.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = comprehend_medical.infer_snomedct(Text=text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     entities = response.get("Entities", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not entities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concepts = entities[0].get("SNOMEDCTConcepts", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Code": c["Code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Description": c["Description"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Score": round(c["Score"], 3)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for c in concepts[:3]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Reconcile Against Existing Problem List
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `reconcile_problems(patient_id, extracted_problems, note_id)`. We compare active extracted problems against the patient's current problem list and produce recommendations: problems to add, problems to resolve, and specificity upgrades.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def reconcile_problems(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     extracted_problems: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_id: str
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Compare extracted active problems against the existing problem list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This produces RECOMMENDATIONS, not changes. Problem list maintenance
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     is a clinical act that requires physician review. We're surfacing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates, not making decisions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Fetch the patient's current active problem list from DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_list = _get_current_problem_list(patient_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_codes = {p["snomed_code"] for p in current_list}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Separate extracted problems by assertion type.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     active_extracted = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         p for p in extracted_problems
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if p["assertion"] == "PRESENT" and p["snomed"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     resolved_signals = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         p for p in extracted_problems
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if p["assertion"] in ("HISTORICAL", "RESOLVED") and p["snomed"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recommendations = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # 1. Find problems active in notes but missing from the problem list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for problem in active_extracted:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         top_snomed = problem["snomed"][0]["Code"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if top_snomed not in current_codes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             recommendations.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "type": "ADD_CANDIDATE",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "problem_text": problem["text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "snomed": problem["snomed"][0],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "icd10": problem["icd10"][0] if problem["icd10"] else None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": problem["confidence"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_note": note_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "rationale": (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     f"Mentioned as active in {problem['section']} section "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     f"but not on current problem list"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # 2. Find problems on the list that notes suggest are resolved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     resolved_codes = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         p["snomed"][0]["Code"] for p in resolved_signals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for existing in current_list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if existing["snomed_code"] in resolved_codes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             recommendations.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "type": "RESOLVE_CANDIDATE",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "problem_text": existing["problem_text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "snomed": {"Code": existing["snomed_code"]},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_note": note_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "rationale": "Mentioned with resolution markers in recent note"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Reconciliation: %d recommendations for patient %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(recommendations), patient_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return recommendations
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _get_current_problem_list(patient_id: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Query DynamoDB for the patient's active problems.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, you'd have a properly designed table with patient_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     as partition key and problem entries as items. This is a simplified
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     query pattern.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(PROBLEMS_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = table.query(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         KeyConditionExpression=boto3.dynamodb.conditions.Key("patient_id").eq(patient_id),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FilterExpression=boto3.dynamodb.conditions.Attr("status").eq("ACTIVE")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return response.get("Items", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 6: Store Results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `store_results(patient_id, extracted_problems, recommendations, note_id)`. We write full extraction results to S3 for audit and reprocessing, and write actionable recommendations to DynamoDB for clinician review workflows.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import uuid
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def store_results(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     extracted_problems: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recommendations: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_id: str
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Persist extraction results and recommendations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Two destinations:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - S3: Full extraction record for audit trail and reprocessing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - DynamoDB: Actionable recommendations for clinician review queue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     timestamp = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the full results record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results_record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "note_id": note_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "extraction_timestamp": timestamp,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "problems_extracted": _serialize_problems(extracted_problems),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "recommendations": recommendations
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Write to S3 for audit trail.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_key = f"results/{patient_id}/{note_id}.json"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_client.put_object(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Bucket=RESULTS_BUCKET,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key=s3_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=json.dumps(results_record, default=str),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ContentType="application/json",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # In production, also specify SSEKMSKeyId with your CMK ARN.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Stored extraction results to s3://%s/%s", RESULTS_BUCKET, s3_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Write recommendations to DynamoDB for clinician review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if recommendations:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rec_table = dynamodb.Table(RECOMMENDATIONS_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for rec in recommendations:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             rec_table.put_item(Item={
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "recommendation_id": str(uuid.uuid4()),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "type": rec["type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "problem_text": rec["problem_text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "snomed_code": rec["snomed"]["Code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "icd10_code": rec.get("icd10", {}).get("Code", "N/A") if rec.get("icd10") else "N/A",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "confidence": Decimal(str(round(rec.get("confidence", 0.0), 3))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_note": note_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "rationale": rec["rationale"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "status": "PENDING_REVIEW",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "created_at": timestamp
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Stored %d recommendations to DynamoDB", len(recommendations))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return results_record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def _serialize_problems(problems: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Prepare problem records for JSON serialization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Strips internal fields (traits, attributes) that are useful during
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     processing but noisy in the final output. Keeps what a reviewer needs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     serialized = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for p in problems:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         serialized.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "text": p["text"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "assertion": p["assertion"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "section": p["section"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "confidence": round(p["confidence"], 3),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "snomed": p.get("snomed"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "icd10": p.get("icd10")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return serialized
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into a single function. In a Lambda deployment, your handler would parse the incoming event (S3 notification or API Gateway request), extract the patient ID and note text, and call this function.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def process_note_for_problems(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_text: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     note_id: str
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full problem list extraction pipeline on a single clinical note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the main entry point. The pipeline:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Detects sections in the note
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Extracts MEDICAL_CONDITION entities from relevant sections
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Classifies assertion status (active, negated, historical, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Normalizes active problems to SNOMED CT and ICD-10 codes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     5. Reconciles against the existing problem list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     6. Stores results and generates recommendations
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns the full extraction record with recommendations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Processing note %s for patient %s", note_id, patient_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1: Split note into sections.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 1: Detecting sections")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sections = detect_sections(note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Found %d sections", len(sections))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 2: Extract clinical problems from each relevant section.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 2: Extracting clinical problems")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     raw_problems = extract_problems(sections)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("  Extracted %d problem mentions", len(raw_problems))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 3: Classify assertion status for each problem.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 3: Classifying assertions")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     classified = classify_assertions(raw_problems)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 4: Normalize active/historical problems to standard codes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 4: Normalizing to SNOMED CT and ICD-10")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     normalized = normalize_problems(classified)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 5: Reconcile against existing problem list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 5: Reconciling against current problem list")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recommendations = reconcile_problems(patient_id, normalized, note_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 6: Store everything.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 6: Storing results")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = store_results(patient_id, normalized, recommendations, note_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Done. Extracted %d problems, %d active, %d recommendations.",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(normalized),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sum(1 for p in normalized if p["assertion"] == "PRESENT"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(recommendations)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # --- Example usage with synthetic data ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m if __name__ == "__main__":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Synthetic clinical note. This mimics a typical progress note with
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # multiple sections and various assertion types.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     SAMPLE_NOTE = """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 62-year-old male with type 2 diabetes and hypertension presents for routine
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m follow-up. Reports good medication adherence. Denies chest pain or shortness
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m of breath. Blood glucose has been well-controlled per home monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PAST MEDICAL HISTORY:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Pneumonia (2023, resolved)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Appendectomy (2015)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m History of smoking, quit 2018
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FAMILY HISTORY:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Mother with breast cancer, diagnosed age 58
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Father with coronary artery disease
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ASSESSMENT AND PLAN:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 1. Type 2 diabetes - well controlled, A1c 6.8%. Continue metformin.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 2. Hypertension - at goal on lisinopril 20mg daily.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 3. Chronic kidney disease stage 3 - stable, Cr 1.6. Continue monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 4. Depression - started on sertraline 3 months ago, reports improvement.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m    PHQ-9 score improved from 14 to 6. Continue current dose.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 5. Obesity - BMI 32. Discussed dietary modifications.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = process_note_for_problems(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id="PAT-2847103",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_text=SAMPLE_NOTE,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         note_id="NOTE-20260301-0482"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2, default=str))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## The Gap Between This and Production
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This example works. Point it at a real Comprehend Medical endpoint with a clinical note and it will extract problems, classify assertions, and produce recommendations. But there's a meaningful distance between "works in a script" and "runs reliably at scale against real patient data." Here's where that gap lives:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Error handling.** Every Comprehend Medical API call can fail: throttling, service errors, malformed input. This code will crash on the first error. A production system wraps each API call in try/except blocks, distinguishes retryable errors (throttling, transient failures) from permanent ones (invalid text encoding), and handles partial failures gracefully (if SNOMED normalization fails but ICD-10 succeeds, you keep the ICD-10 result).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Retries and backoff.** The `adaptive` retry mode handles basic throttling, but Comprehend Medical's rate limits are per-region, and a batch job processing thousands of notes will hit them. Production systems implement explicit rate limiting (token bucket or leaky bucket) on top of boto3's built-in retries, with exponential backoff and jitter for burst tolerance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Input validation.** This code trusts that the note text is valid UTF-8 under 20,000 characters. Real clinical notes come from HL7 feeds, EHR extracts, and FHIR bundles in various encodings. Production code validates encoding, strips control characters, checks length against Comprehend Medical's limits, and handles the case where a note is too long by intelligently chunking at section boundaries rather than cutting mid-sentence.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Structured logging.** The `logger.info` calls here are a starting point. Production needs structured JSON logging with consistent fields: patient_id, note_id, step, duration_ms, entity_count, error details. This is what powers your monitoring dashboards and what your on-call engineer queries at 2am when extraction accuracy drops.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IAM least-privilege.** The IAM role for this Lambda should have exactly: `comprehendmedical:DetectEntitiesV2`, `comprehendmedical:InferICD10CM`, `comprehendmedical:InferSNOMEDCT` (all resources), `s3:GetObject` and `s3:PutObject` scoped to specific bucket prefixes, `dynamodb:PutItem` and `dynamodb:Query` scoped to specific tables. Not `comprehendmedical:*`. Not `s3:*`.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **VPC and VPC endpoints.** Clinical notes contain PHI. In production, this Lambda runs in a VPC with private subnets and VPC endpoints for Comprehend Medical, S3, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs. Traffic stays on the AWS backbone. No public internet traversal, even though everything is TLS-encrypted in transit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **KMS customer-managed keys.** This example uses `ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms"` but doesn't specify a key ID, which means it uses the AWS-managed key. Production uses a CMK you control, with key rotation enabled, and CloudTrail logging every key usage event.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **DynamoDB Decimal handling.** DynamoDB doesn't accept Python floats. This example already wraps confidence scores in `Decimal(str(...))`. Any new numeric fields must follow the same pattern. If you forget, `put_item` raises a `TypeError` that's not immediately obvious in its error message.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Section detection robustness.** The regex-based section detection here works for cleanly formatted notes. Real clinical notes are messy: inconsistent casing, missing colons, headers embedded mid-paragraph, numbered lists that look like headers. Production systems use ML-based section detectors trained on diverse note formats, or at minimum a much more comprehensive pattern library.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Comprehend Medical API limits.** DetectEntitiesV2 accepts up to 20,000 UTF-8 characters per call. Discharge summaries and operative notes routinely exceed this. Production systems chunk long notes at section boundaries and reassemble results with corrected offsets. The chunking strategy matters: splitting mid-sentence can break negation scope.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Testing.** There are no tests here. Production needs unit tests for section detection (with diverse note formats), integration tests against Comprehend Medical with known test notes, assertion classification tests with manually annotated examples covering negation edge cases, and end-to-end tests that verify the full pipeline produces expected recommendations. Use synthetic notes only. Never put real patient text in your test fixtures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Reconciliation complexity.** The reconciliation logic here does simple code matching. Real reconciliation needs SNOMED hierarchy traversal (is "Type 2 diabetes mellitus" a parent of "Type 2 diabetes mellitus with diabetic nephropathy"?), fuzzy concept matching for cases where the extracted text doesn't normalize perfectly, and deduplication logic for when the same problem appears in multiple notes with slightly different wording.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
